    <sect3 role="installation">
      <title>Installation of gi-docgen</title>

    <!-- https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gi-docgen/-/issues/188 -->
    <para>
      Silence a warning from the Graphviz <command>dot</command> utility
      which will cause documentation of various packages fail to build
      if Graphviz is installed but built without Pango, and
      <command>gi-docgen</command> is invoked with the
      <option>--fatal-warnings</option> option:
    </para>

    <screen><userinput>sed -i '/if err:/s/err/proc.returncode/' gidocgen/utils.py</userinput></screen>

    <para> Build the module: </para>

&build-wheel;

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>&install-wheel; gi-docgen</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      To test the installation, issue <command>pytest</command>.
    </para>

    </sect3>

